{"title_page": "Idris Jusoh", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Like resume|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Dato' Sri|Dato' Seri]] [[Hajji|Haji]]\n| name = Idris Jusoh\n| native_name = \u0625\u062f\u0631\u064a\u0633 \u0628\u0646 \u062c\u0648\u0633\u0648\u0647\n| honorific-suffix = [[Order of Sultan Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu|SSMZ]] [[Order of the Crown of Terengganu|DPMT]] [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Terengganu#Meritorious Service Medal|PJK]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image = DSIJ Side Profile.JPG\n| office = [[Minister of Higher Education (Malaysia)|Minister of Higher Education]]\n| term_start = 29 July 2015\n| term_end = 10 May 2018\n| primeminister = [[Najib Razak]]\n| monarch = [[Abdul Halim of Kedah|Abdul Halim]]<br />[[Muhammad V of Kelantan|Muhammad V]]\n| constituency = [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]]\n| deputy = [[Mary Yap Kain Ching]]\n| predecessor = ''Himself'' {{small|as Minister of Education II}}\n| successor = [[Maszlee Malik]] {{small|as Minister of Education}}\n| office1 = [[Minister of Education (Malaysia)|Minister of Education II]]\n| term_start1 = 16 May 2013\n| term_end1 = 29 July 2015\n| constituency1 = Besut\n| primeminister1 = Najib Razak\n| alongside1 = [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| successor1 = ''Himself'' {{small|as Minister of Higher Education}}\n| deputy1 = 1. [[P. Kamalanathan|Kamalanathan Panchanathan]]<br />2. Mary Yap Kain Ching\n| monarch1 = Abdul Halim\n| predecessor1 = [[Mohamed Khaled Nordin]] {{small|as Minister of Higher Education}}\n| order2 = 12th\n| office2 = Menteri Besar of Terengganu\n| term_start2 = 25 March 2004\n| term_end2 = 25 March 2008\n| predecessor2 = [[Abdul Hadi Awang]]\n| constituency2 = [[Jerteh|Jertih]]\n| deputy2 = \n| monarch2 = [[Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu|Mizan Zainal Abidin]]\n| successor2 = [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]]\n| office3 = Chairman of [[Majlis Amanah Rakyat]]\n| term_start3 = 17 July 2008\n| term_end3 = 9 March 2013\n| predecessor3 = \n| successor3 = \n| minister3 = [[Muhammad Muhammad Taib]] (2008-2009)<br />[[Shafie Apdal]] (2009-2013)\n| constituency_MP4 = [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]]\n| parliament4 = Malaysian\n| term_start4 = 5 May 2013\n| term_end4 = \n| majority4 = 8,342 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])<br />4,599 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n| predecessor4 = [[Abdullah Md Zin]] ([[United Malay National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor4 =\n| term_start5 = 1995\n| term_end5 = 1999\n| predecessor5 = [[Mohamed Yusof Mohamed Noor]] ([[United Malay National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor5 = Hassan Mohamed ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]]-[[Barisan Alternatif|BA]])\n| majority5 = 4,507 ([[1995 Malaysian general election|1995]])\n| constituency_AM6 = [[Jerteh|Jertih]]\n| assembly6 = Terengganu State Legislative\n| term_start6 = 2004\n| term_end6 = 2013\n| predecessor6 = [[Mohd Salleh Abas]]\n| successor6 = Muhammad Pehimi Yusof\n| majority6 = 2,047 ([[2004 Malaysian general election|2004]])<br />3,046 ([[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]])\n| birth_name = Idris bin Jusoh\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1955|11|15}}\n| birth_place =  Kampung Tok Has, [[Jerteh|Jertih]], [[Besut]], [[Terengganu]], [[Federation of Malaya]] (now [[Malaysia]])\n| citizenship = [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]]\n| otherparty = [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN)\n| party = [[United Malay National Organisation]] (UMNO)\n| spouse = Che Kamariah Zakaria\n| alma_mater = [[Universiti Sains Malaysia]]<br />[[Aston University]]<br />[[University of New Haven]]<br />[[University of Jordan]]<br />[[Harvard University]]\n| website = [http://www.idrisjusoh.com www.idrisjusoh.com]\n}}\n\n[[Malay titles#Dato' Sri|Dato' Seri]] [[Hajji|Haji]] '''Idris bin Jusoh''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u0625\u062f\u0631\u064a\u0633 \u0628\u0646 \u062c\u0648\u0633\u0648\u0647; born 15 November 1955) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] [[politician]] and [[Member of Parliament]] of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] for [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]] constituency. He was the [[Minister of Higher Education (Malaysia)|Minister of Higher Education]] from July 2015 to May 2018. He is a former [[Menteri Besar of Terengganu]] and also the former Chairman of [[Majlis Amanah Rakyat]] (MARA). He is a member of the [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO) which is part of the national opposition coalition [[Barisan Nasional]].\n\n==Early life ==\nIdris Jusoh or popularly known as \"Yeh\" (Yeh is just a shortform for Idris, most Kelantanese call people with the name Idris as Yeh and Jertih, at least according to some folklores, used to belong to Kelantan) attended elite school (STAR) from 1968 to 1973.\n\nYeh was in Green House. He was a school prefect too. He was one of the best students in STAR during his time. Those days, best students were sent to Australia for matriculation even before the MCE(SPM) results were known. And he was one of them.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.staroba.my/old-boys/1634-do-you-know-idris-jusoh.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-06-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140115065418/http://www.staroba.my/old-boys/1634-do-you-know-idris-jusoh.html |archivedate=15 January 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nHe came back to Malaysia before completing his studies in Australia because his father died. Later on he attended USM and was at one time USM's \"overall best student\".\n\nYeh became famous when he won Terengganu for Barisan Nasional from PAS in 2004 and he became the state MB. PAS, the incumbent party, won only 4 seats while Idris-led BN conquered 28.\n\nHe was MARA chairman until his recent appointment as Minister of Education II. Yeh is married to a Kelantanese lady whom he met in USM.\n\n==Education background==\n*Primary: SK Seberang Jerteh, Terengganu (1962-1968)\n*Secondary: [[Sekolah Tuanku Abdul Rahman]] (STAR) Ipoh (1968-1973)\n*[[Blackburn High School]], Victoria, Australia (1974)\n*Bachelor in Social Sciences (Economics), [[Universiti Sains Malaysia]] (1980)\n*Entrepreneurship Course, [[Aston University|University of Aston]], England (1984)\n*Masters in Business Administration (MBA) (Finance), [[University of New Haven]], USA (1988)\n*Arabic language studies, [[University of Jordan]] (1994)\n*Advanced Management Programme, INSEAD, France (2008)\n*\"Leaders In Developing Countries\" Programme - Havard Kennedy School of Executive Education, Massachusetts, USA (2009)\n\n==Political career==\n===Highest position (government/private)===\n*Minister of Higher Education  (July 2015 \u2013 2018) \n*Minister of Education II (May 2013 \u2013 July 2015)\n*Chairman of MARA (August 2008 \u2013 April 2013)\n*Chief Minister of Terengganu (2004 \u2013 2008)\n*Terengganu State Assemblyman (Constituency of Jerteh) (2004-2013)\n*Chairman, Board of Directors Ketengah (2000-2008)\n*Deputy Minister, Ministry of Entrepreneurial Development (1995 -1999)\n*Besut Member of Parliament (1995 \u2013 1999) (2013 \u2013present) \n*MARA council member (1991 \u2013 1993)\n*Managing Director, Jusoh Enterprise (1988 \u2013 1995)\n*Managing Director, Jusoh Sawmill (1980\u20131986)\n\n===Highest position (politic)===\n* UMNO Supreme Council Member (2000\u20132018)\n* Chairman of Coordination Council, UMNO Negeri Terengganu (2004- 2008)\n* Chairman of Barisan Nasional Terengganu Committee (2004- 2008)\n* Division Chief, UMNO Besut (2000 \u2013 2013)\n* Division Youth Chief, UMNO Terengganu (1992-1993)\n* Division Youth Chief, UMNO Besut (1985-1995)\n\n===Terengganu===\nFollowing the [[2008 Malaysian general election]], [[Barisan Nasional]] managed to win a majority in the [[Terengganu]] state election, garnering 24 out of 32 state seats on offer, with [[PAS (political party)|PAS]] winning the remaining 8 seats.\n\nIn the formation of the new Terengganu state government, the federal government under the then [[Prime Minister of Malaysia|Prime Minister]] [[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]] recommended Idris Jusoh as ''Menteri Besar'', who received full support of twenty-three of the 24 Barisan Nasional state assemblymen elected.<ref>{{cite news| title =23 Terengganu Assemblymen Pledge Support For Idris Jusoh| publisher= Bernama| url =http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=322230}}</ref>\n\nA crisis soon ensued after the [[Sultan of Terengganu]], [[Mizan Zainal Abidin]], who is also the [[Yang di-Pertuan Agong]] (Supreme Ruler) of Malaysia, refused to re-appoint and swear in Idris as Menteri Besar. On 22 March 2008, the office of the [[Sultan of Terengganu]] announced the appointment of [[Kijal]] assemblyman [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] instead of Idris Jusoh.<ref>{{cite news| title =Malaysia: The MB For Terengganu Finally Appointed| publisher= Sin Chew| url =http://www.mysinchew.com/node/8893?tid=4}}</ref>\n\nThe Prime Minister responded by saying that the appointment of Ahmad Said was unconstitutional as it went against the wishes of the assemblymen and the Prime Minister's office who have supported Idris Jusoh candidacy for ''Menteri Besar''.<ref>{{cite news| title =Terengganu MB Appointment Unconstitutional, Says Abdullah| publisher= Bernama| url =http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=322201}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2008/3/24/nation/20733338&sec=nation|publisher=The Star|title=PM: Appointing anyone else is against Constitution|date=24 March 2008|accessdate=24 March 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080409203437/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2008%2F3%2F24%2Fnation%2F20733338&sec=nation|archivedate=9 April 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The 22 other BN assemblymen had also pledged their support toward the appointment of Idris Jusoh according to Deputy Prime Minister [[Najib Tun Razak]].<ref>{{cite news|title=23 Terengganu Assemblymen Pledge Support For Idris Jusoh, Says Najib|publisher=Bernama|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=322230|date=24 March 2008|accessdate=24 March 2008}}</ref> [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] was given warning that he would be stripped of his UMNO membership \"for disobeying the party's leadership\". However he was not stripped of his UMNO membership<ref>{{cite news |date=23 March 2008 |accessdate=23 March 2008 |title=Sultan's choice of MB stripped of Umno membership |publisher=The Star |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2008/3/23/nation/20730032 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090201035216/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2008%2F3%2F23%2Fnation%2F20730032 |url-status=dead |archive-date=1 February 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March 2008, Prime Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi and Sultan [[Mizan Zainal Abidin]] met at [[Istana Negara, Jalan Istana|Istana Negara]] to resolve the impasse. The Prime Minister accepted the King's appointment of [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] as Menteri Besar of Terengganu. He also apologised to the King for the public spat over the appointment of the mentri besar, explaining that there was no intention to disparage or humiliate the royal household. This apparent backdown was due to threat that the royal household would be prepared to dissolve the state assembly if there had been a motion of no-confidence against [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] by the 22 Umno state assemblymen.<ref>{{cite news |date=26 March 2008 |accessdate=26 March 2008 |title=What it means to be world class |publisher=[[The Malaysian Insider]] |url=http://themalaysianinsider.com/mni/ahmad-said-to-stay-on-as-mb.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080329211011/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/mni/ahmad-said-to-stay-on-as-mb.html |archivedate=29 March 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe crisis was one of the only royal interventions in Malaysia in recent times.\n\nOn 10 September 2013, referring to the National Education Blueprint, he made a highlight in the news by saying this in a forum in Sabah, \"If some people feel the system is not good and want to send their children overseas to study, the government cannot stop them. But the Ministry will work towards improving the country\u2019s education system,\"\n\nOn 21 February 2015, he declared that Malaysia's higher education is now on par with those of developed nations including the United Kingdom, Germany and Australia, said Second Education Minister Datuk Seri Idris Jusoh. He said this was proven by the fact that 135,000 foreign students made up 10% of students at national higher educational institutions in the country. This statement was largely criticized due to its over optimism. On 24 February 2015, Idris released an article entitled \"What it Means to be World Class\" to explain the statement as we as other education matters.<ref>{{cite news |date=25 Feb 2015 |accessdate=7 July 2017 |title =What it means to be world class |author =Idris Jusoh | publisher= [[Malaysiakini]]| url =https://m.malaysiakini.com/news/290169}}</ref>\n\n==Social contributions==\n* Global Sciences and Innovation Advisory Council(GSIAC) member (2013 \u2013 present)\n* Member, Bumiputera Agenda Action Council (MTAB) -(Februari 2011\u2013 present)\n* Member, Pahang State Economic Advisory Council (2012\u2013 present)\n* Deputy Chairman, UMNO Malaysia Economic Bureau (2008\u2013present)\n* Member, Yayasan IQRA Board of Trustees (2011 \u2013 present)\n* Chairman, 4th Bumiputera Economic Congress (1999)\n* Chairman, Tunku Abdul Rahman Foundation (2012-sekarang)\n* Founder, MIND Centre (Mindset), Besut  (2008)\n* Founder, IMTIAZ schools & Board of Trustees (1999)\n* Founder, Pintar Quran Board of Directors (1994)\n* Founder, Ulul Albab Programme (2006)\n* Founder, Fulbright Scholars English Teaching Assistants Programme (2006)\n\n==Awards ==\n*President of the USM Students Council (1978-1979)\n*Gold Medal Award Recipient for being Best Student in USM (1980)\n*President of the International Student Association in University New Haven, USA (1987)\n*Best Club Award, Youth Entrepreneurship Clubs (1994)\n*Special Appreciation Award : Individual Malaysian Franchise Award (2000/2001)\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Terengganu State Legislative Assembly]]: N03 [[Jertih (state constituency)|Jertih]]'''\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opponent(s)\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2004 Malaysian general election|2004]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Idris Jusoh'''}} ([[United Malays National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n|align=\"right\" |'''6,513'''\n|'''%'''\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Mohd Hassan Salleh ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |4,466\n|%\n|11,119\n|2,047\n|85%\n|-\n|[[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Idris Jusoh'''}} ([[United Malays National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n|align=\"right\" |'''7,912'''\n|'''%'''\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Muhammad Hassan Salleh ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |4,866\n|%\n|12,953\n|3,046\n|84%\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]''': P33 [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]], Terengganu\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|Government\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opposition\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[1995 Malaysian general election|1995]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Idris Jusoh'''}} ([[United Malays National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n|align=\"right\" |'''19,294'''\n|'''56.61%'''\n|{{Party shading/S46}} |\n|Zakaria @ Ibrahim Abdul Rahman ([[Semangat 46|S46]])\n|align=\"right\" |25,098\n|43.39%\n|35,437\n|4,507\n|81.37%\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Idris Jusoh'''}} ([[United Malays National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n|align=\"right\" |'''35,232'''\n|'''56.71%'''\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Riduan Mohamad Nor ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |26,890\n|43.29%\n|63,017\n|8,342\n|86.84%\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]]\n| rowspan=2 {{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n| rowspan=2|{{nowrap|'''Idris Jusoh'''}} ([[United Malays National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n| rowspan=2 align=\"right\"|'''34,335'''\n| rowspan=2|'''48.40%'''\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Riduan Mohamad Nor ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |29,736\n|41.92%\n| rowspan=2|72,323\n| rowspan=2|4,599\n| rowspan=2|83.49%\n|-\n|{{Party shading/Keadilan}} |\n|Wan Nazari Wan Jusoh  ([[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|PPBM]])\n|align=\"right\" |6,864\n|9.68%\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* {{Flag|Terengganu}} :\n** [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Terengganu#Meritorious Service Medal|Meritorious Service Medal]] (PJK) (1994)\n** [[File:MY-TER Order of the Crown of Terengganu - Dato Paduka - DPMT.svg|50px]] Knight Commander of the [[Order of the Crown of Terengganu]] (DPMT) - '''Dato'''' (1998)<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.istiadat.gov.my/index.php/component/semakanlantikanskp/|title=SEMAKAN PENERIMA DARJAH KEBESARAN, BINTANG DAN PINGAT|publisher=[[Prime Minister's Department (Malaysia)]]|accessdate=25 October 2018}}</ref>\n** [[File:MY-TER Order of Sultan Mizan Zainal Abidin - Dato Sri Setia - SSMZ.svg|50px]] Knight Grand Companion of the [[Order of Sultan Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu]] (SSMZ) - '''Dato' Seri''' (2004)<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{cite web|date=20 July 2004|accessdate=30 October 2018|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2004/07/20/sultan-of-terengganus-birthday-honours-list/|title=Sultan of Terengganu's birthday honours list}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Besut (federal constituency)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box|\nbefore=[[Abdul Hadi Awang]]|\ntitle=[[List of Menteris Besar of Terengganu|Menteri Besar of Terengganu]]|\nyears=25 March 2004 \u2013 25 March 2008|\nafter=[[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Terengganu-FedRep}}\n{{Second Najib cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jusoh, Idris}}\n[[Category:Chief Ministers of Terengganu]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:United Malays National Organisation politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:People from Terengganu]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Aston University]]\n[[Category:University of New Haven alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Jordan alumni]]\n[[Category:John F. Kennedy School of Government alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Members of the Terengganu State Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Terengganu state executive councillors]]\n[[Category:Education ministers of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian people]]\n<!-- Honours -->\n[[Category:Knights Commander of the Order of the Crown of Terengganu]]\n[[Category:Universiti Sains Malaysia alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Like resume|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Dato' Sri|Dato' Seri]] [[Hajji|Haji]]\n| name = Idris Jusoh\n| native_name = \u0625\u062f\u0631\u064a\u0633 \u0628\u0646 \u062c\u0648\u0633\u0648\u0647\n| honorific-suffix = [[Order of Sultan Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu|SSMZ]] [[Order of the Crown of Terengganu|DPMT]] [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Terengganu#Meritorious Service Medal|PJK]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image = DSIJ Side Profile.JPG\n| office = [[Minister of Higher Education (Malaysia)|Minister of Higher Education]]\n| term_start = 29 July 2015\n| term_end = 10 May 2018\n| primeminister = [[Najib Razak]]\n| monarch = [[Abdul Halim of Kedah|Abdul Halim]]<br />[[Muhammad V of Kelantan|Muhammad V]]\n| constituency = [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]]\n| deputy = [[Mary Yap Kain Ching]]\n| predecessor = ''Himself'' {{small|as Minister of Education II}}\n| successor = [[Maszlee Malik]] {{small|as Minister of Education}}\n| office1 = [[Minister of Education (Malaysia)|Minister of Education II]]\n| term_start1 = 16 May 2013\n| term_end1 = 29 July 2015\n| constituency1 = Besut\n| primeminister1 = Najib Razak\n| alongside1 = [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| successor1 = ''Himself'' {{small|as Minister of Higher Education}}\n| deputy1 = 1. [[P. Kamalanathan|Kamalanathan Panchanathan]]<br />2. Mary Yap Kain Ching\n| monarch1 = Abdul Halim\n| predecessor1 = [[Mohamed Khaled Nordin]] {{small|as Minister of Higher Education}}\n| order2 = 12th\n| office2 = Menteri Besar of Terengganu\n| term_start2 = 25 March 2004\n| term_end2 = 25 March 2008\n| predecessor2 = [[Abdul Hadi Awang]]\n| constituency2 = [[Jerteh|Jertih]]\n| deputy2 = \n| monarch2 = [[Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu|Mizan Zainal Abidin]]\n| successor2 = [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]]\n| office3 = Chairman of [[Majlis Amanah Rakyat]]\n| term_start3 = 17 July 2008\n| term_end3 = 9 March 2013\n| predecessor3 = \n| successor3 = \n| minister3 = [[Muhammad Muhammad Taib]] (2008-2009)<br />[[Shafie Apdal]] (2009-2013)\n| constituency_MP4 = [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]]\n| parliament4 = Malaysian\n| term_start4 = 5 May 2013\n| term_end4 = \n| majority4 = 8,342 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])<br />4,599 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n| predecessor4 = [[Abdullah Md Zin]] ([[United Malay National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor4 =\n| term_start5 = 1995\n| term_end5 = 1999\n| predecessor5 = [[Mohamed Yusof Mohamed Noor]] ([[United Malay National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor5 = Hassan Mohamed ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]]-[[Barisan Alternatif|BA]])\n| majority5 = 4,507 ([[1995 Malaysian general election|1995]])\n| constituency_AM6 = [[Jerteh|Jertih]]\n| assembly6 = Terengganu State Legislative\n| term_start6 = 2004\n| term_end6 = 2013\n| predecessor6 = [[Mohd Salleh Abas]]\n| successor6 = Muhammad Pehimi Yusof\n| majority6 = 2,047 ([[2004 Malaysian general election|2004]])<br />3,046 ([[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]])\n| birth_name = Idris bin Jusoh\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1955|11|15}}\n| birth_place =  Kampung Tok Has, [[Jerteh|Jertih]], [[Besut]], [[Terengganu]], [[Federation of Malaya]] (now [[Malaysia]])\n| citizenship = [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]]\n| otherparty = [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN)\n| party = [[United Malay National Organisation]] (UMNO)\n| spouse = Che Kamariah Zakaria\n| alma_mater = [[Universiti Sains Malaysia]]<br />[[Aston University]]<br />[[University of New Haven]]<br />[[University of Jordan]]<br />[[Harvard University]]\n| website = [http://www.idrisjusoh.com www.idrisjusoh.com]\n}}\n\n[[Malay titles#Dato' Sri|Dato' Seri]] [[Hajji|Haji]] '''Idris bin Jusoh''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u0625\u062f\u0631\u064a\u0633 \u0628\u0646 \u062c\u0648\u0633\u0648\u0647; born 15 November 1955) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] [[politician]] and [[Member of Parliament]] of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] for [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]] constituency. He was the [[Minister of Higher Education (Malaysia)|Minister of Higher Education]] from July 2015 to May 2018. He is a former [[Menteri Besar of Terengganu]] and also the former Chairman of [[Majlis Amanah Rakyat]] (MARA). He is a member of the [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO) which is part of the national opposition coalition [[Barisan Nasional]].\n\n==Early life ==\nIdris Jusoh or popularly known as \"Yeh\" (Yeh is just a shortform for Idris, most Kelantanese call people with the name Idris as Yeh and Jertih, at least according to some folklores, used to belong to Kelantan) attended elite school (STAR) from 1968 to 1973.\n\nYeh was in Green House. He was a school prefect too. He was one of the best students in STAR during his time. Those days, best students were sent to Australia for matriculation even before the MCE(SPM) results were known. And he was one of them.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.staroba.my/old-boys/1634-do-you-know-idris-jusoh.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-06-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140115065418/http://www.staroba.my/old-boys/1634-do-you-know-idris-jusoh.html |archivedate=15 January 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nHe came back to Malaysia before completing his studies in Australia because his father died. Later on he attended USM and was at one time USM's \"overall best student\".\n\nYeh became famous when he won Terengganu for Barisan Nasional from PAS in 2004 and he became the state MB. PAS, the incumbent party, won only 4 seats while Idris-led BN conquered 28.\n\nHe was MARA chairman until his recent appointment as Minister of Education II. Yeh is married to a Kelantanese lady whom he met in USM.\n\n==Education background==\n*Primary: SK Seberang Jerteh, Terengganu (1962-1968)\n*Secondary: [[Sekolah Tuanku Abdul Rahman]] (STAR) Ipoh (1968-1973)\n*[[Blackburn High School]], Victoria, Australia (1974)\n*Bachelor in Social Sciences (Economics), [[Universiti Sains Malaysia]] (1980)\n*Entrepreneurship Course, [[Aston University|University of Aston]], England (1984)\n*Masters in Business Administration (MBA) (Finance), [[University of New Haven]], USA (1988)\n*Arabic language studies, [[University of Jordan]] (1994)\n*Advanced Management Programme, INSEAD, France (2008)\n*\"Leaders In Developing Countries\" Programme - Havard Kennedy School of Executive Education, Massachusetts, USA (2009)\n\n==Political career==\n===Highest position (government/private)===\n*Minister of Higher Education  (July 2015 \u2013 2018) \n*Minister of Education II (May 2013 \u2013 July 2015)\n*Chairman of MARA (August 2008 \u2013 April 2013)\n*Chief Minister of Terengganu (2004 \u2013 2008)\n*Terengganu State Assemblyman (Constituency of Jerteh) (2004-2013)\n*Chairman, Board of Directors Ketengah (2000-2008)\n*Deputy Minister, Ministry of Entrepreneurial Development (1995 -1999)\n*Besut Member of Parliament (1995 \u2013 1999) (2013 \u2013present) \n*MARA council member (1991 \u2013 1993)\n*Managing Director, Jusoh Enterprise (1988 \u2013 1995)\n*Managing Director, Jusoh Sawmill (1980\u20131986)\n\n===Highest position (politic)===\n* UMNO Supreme Council Member (2000\u20132018)\n* Chairman of Coordination Council, UMNO Negeri Terengganu (2004- 2008)\n* Chairman of Barisan Nasional Terengganu Committee (2004- 2008)\n* Division Chief, UMNO Besut (2000 \u2013 2013)\n* Division Youth Chief, UMNO Terengganu (1992-1993)\n* Division Youth Chief, UMNO Besut (1985-1995)\n\n===Terengganu===\nFollowing the [[2008 Malaysian general election]], [[Barisan Nasional]] managed to win a majority in the [[Terengganu]] state election, garnering 24 out of 32 state seats on offer, with [[PAS (political party)|PAS]] winning the remaining 8 seats.\n\nIn the formation of the new Terengganu state government, the federal government under the then [[Prime Minister of Malaysia|Prime Minister]] [[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]] recommended Idris Jusoh as ''Menteri Besar'', who received full support of twenty-three of the 24 Barisan Nasional state assemblymen elected.<ref>{{cite news| title =23 Terengganu Assemblymen Pledge Support For Idris Jusoh| publisher= Bernama| url =http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=322230}}</ref>\n\nA crisis soon ensued after the [[Sultan of Terengganu]], [[Mizan Zainal Abidin]], who is also the [[Yang di-Pertuan Agong]] (Supreme Ruler) of Malaysia, refused to re-appoint and swear in Idris as Menteri Besar. On 22 March 2008, the office of the [[Sultan of Terengganu]] announced the appointment of [[Kijal]] assemblyman [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] instead of Idris Jusoh.<ref>{{cite news| title =Malaysia: The MB For Terengganu Finally Appointed| publisher= Sin Chew| url =http://www.mysinchew.com/node/8893?tid=4}}</ref>\n\nThe Prime Minister responded by saying that the appointment of Ahmad Said was unconstitutional as it went against the wishes of the assemblymen and the Prime Minister's office who have supported Idris Jusoh candidacy for ''Menteri Besar''.<ref>{{cite news| title =Terengganu MB Appointment Unconstitutional, Says Abdullah| publisher= Bernama| url =http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=322201}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2008/3/24/nation/20733338&sec=nation|publisher=The Star|title=PM: Appointing anyone else is against Constitution|date=24 March 2008|accessdate=24 March 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080409203437/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2008%2F3%2F24%2Fnation%2F20733338&sec=nation|archivedate=9 April 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The 22 other BN assemblymen had also pledged their support toward the appointment of Idris Jusoh according to Deputy Prime Minister [[Najib Tun Razak]].<ref>{{cite news|title=23 Terengganu Assemblymen Pledge Support For Idris Jusoh, Says Najib|publisher=Bernama|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=322230|date=24 March 2008|accessdate=24 March 2008}}</ref> [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] was given warning that he would be stripped of his UMNO membership \"for disobeying the party's leadership\". However he was not stripped of his UMNO membership<ref>{{cite news |date=23 March 2008 |accessdate=23 March 2008 |title=Sultan's choice of MB stripped of Umno membership |publisher=The Star |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2008/3/23/nation/20730032 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090201035216/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2008%2F3%2F23%2Fnation%2F20730032 |url-status=dead |archive-date=1 February 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March 2008, Prime Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi and Sultan [[Mizan Zainal Abidin]] met at [[Istana Negara, Jalan Istana|Istana Negara]] to resolve the impasse. The Prime Minister accepted the King's appointment of [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] as Menteri Besar of Terengganu. He also apologised to the King for the public spat over the appointment of the mentri besar, explaining that there was no intention to disparage or humiliate the royal household. This apparent backdown was due to threat that the royal household would be prepared to dissolve the state assembly if there had been a motion of no-confidence against [[Ahmad Said (politician)|Ahmad Said]] by the 22 Umno state assemblymen.<ref>{{cite news |date=26 March 2008 |accessdate=26 March 2008 |title=What it means to be world class |publisher=[[The Malaysian Insider]] |url=http://themalaysianinsider.com/mni/ahmad-said-to-stay-on-as-mb.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080329211011/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/mni/ahmad-said-to-stay-on-as-mb.html |archivedate=29 March 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe crisis was one of the only royal interventions in Malaysia in recent times.\n\nOn 10 September 2013, referring to the National Education Blueprint, he made a highlight in the news by saying this in a forum in Sabah, \"If some people feel the system is not good and want to send their children overseas to study, the government cannot stop them. But the Ministry will work towards improving the country\u2019s education system,\"\n\nOn 21 February 2015, he declared that Malaysia's higher education is now on par with those of developed nations including the United Kingdom, Germany and Australia, said Second Education Minister Datuk Seri Idris Jusoh. He said this was proven by the fact that 135,000 foreign students made up 10% of students at national higher educational institutions in the country. This statement was largely criticized due to its over optimism. On 24 February 2015, Idris released an article entitled \"What it Means to be World Class\" to explain the statement as we as other education matters.<ref>{{cite news |date=25 Feb 2015 |accessdate=7 July 2017 |title =What it means to be world class |author =Idris Jusoh | publisher= [[Malaysiakini]]| url =https://m.malaysiakini.com/news/290169}}</ref>\n\n==Social contributions==\n* Global Sciences and Innovation Advisory Council(GSIAC) member (2013 \u2013 present)\n* Member, Bumiputera Agenda Action Council (MTAB) -(Februari 2011\u2013 present)\n* Member, Pahang State Economic Advisory Council (2012\u2013 present)\n* Deputy Chairman, UMNO Malaysia Economic Bureau (2008\u2013present)\n* Member, Yayasan IQRA Board of Trustees (2011 \u2013 present)\n* Chairman, 4th Bumiputera Economic Congress (1999)\n* Chairman, Tunku Abdul Rahman Foundation (2012-sekarang)\n* Founder, MIND Centre (Mindset), Besut  (2008)\n* Founder, IMTIAZ schools & Board of Trustees (1999)\n* Founder, Pintar Quran Board of Directors (1994)\n* Founder, Ulul Albab Programme (2006)\n* Founder, Fulbright Scholars English Teaching Assistants Programme (2006)\n\n==Awards ==\n*President of the USM Students Council (1978-1979)\n*Gold Medal Award Recipient for being Best Student in USM (1980)\n*President of the International Student Association in University New Haven, USA (1987)\n*Best Club Award, Youth Entrepreneurship Clubs (1994)\n*Special Appreciation Award : Individual Malaysian Franchise Award (2000/2001)\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Terengganu State Legislative Assembly]]: [[Jertih (state constituency)|Jertih]]'''\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opponent(s)\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2004 Malaysian g