 the Zoo!\"\n* [[Clownfish]]\n* [[Mandrill]]\n\n===Season 3===\n1.\"Stanley's Dinosaur Roundup\"\n*''[[Brachiosaurus]]''\n\n2. \"To Catch a Hamster / Pearls of Wisdom\"\n* [[Hamster]]\n* [[Oyster]]\n\n3. \"Living with Leopards / A Chinese New Year\"\n* [[Leopard]]\\[[Snow leopard]]\n* [[Chinese zodiac]]\n\n4. \"A Turkey of a Thangskiving\"\n*[[Domestic turkey]]\n*[[Wild turkey]]\n\n5. \"The Way of the Buffalo / Follow That Falcon\"\n* [[Bison]]\n* [[Peregrine falcon]]\n\n6. \"Shell Game / Sheep and a Haircut\"\n* [[Painted turtle]]\n* [[Sheep]]\n\n7. \"No News Like Shoe News / Ladybug, Ladybug\"\n* [[Snowshoe hare]]\n* [[Ladybug]]\n\n8. \"Curse of the Angry Coral / A Little Bird Told Me\"\n* [[Coral]]\n* [[Cedar waxwing]]\n\n9. \"Stanley's Great Big Book of Adventure\"\n* [[Jackrabbit]]\n* [[Snowy owl]]\n* [[Blue whale]]\n* [[Asian elephant]]\n* [[Llama]]\n* [[Orca]]\n\n===TV specials===\n# \"Little Dog Lost\" (Christmas)\n# \"Grandma Griff's Mystery Guest\" (Halloween)\n# \"A Turkey of a Thanksgiving\" (Thanksgiving)\n# \"Stanley's Great Big Book of Everything Adventure\"\n\n==Broadcast history==\nIn the U.S., the series aired on Disney Channel's daytime preschool block [[Playhouse Disney]] since its debut, September 15, 2001. When Playhouse Disney rebranded its on-air presentation in 2007, ''Stanley'' was put on a new timeslot at 6:00 AM ET on the weekdays. As of May 2008, ''Stanley'' no longer airs on Playhouse Disney, but DVDs and books are still available. In February 2011, the show was completely removed when Playhouse Disney rebranded as [[Disney Junior]]. The show was briefly seen online on DisneyJunior.com as part of \"fan favorites\" week on the week of June 20, 2011. From March 23, 2012 to September 3, 2013, the series returned on the U.S. airwaves on [[Disney Junior]].\n\nIn Canada, it ran on The Family Channel from 2002 to 2007 and then was moved to Disney Junior, which has been running since 2007. It also aired on the Canadian-French version of Disney Junior since 2010.\n\n===Canada===\n*[[Family Channel (Canadian TV network)|Family (Canada)]] (2002 - November 29, 2007)\n*[[Family Jr.|Disney Junior (English Canada)]] (May 6, 2011 - September 29, 2013)\n*[[T\u00e9l\u00e9magino|Disney Junior (French Canada)]] (May 6, 2011 - 2015)\n*[[Family Jr.|Playhouse Disney (English Canada)]] (November 30, 2007 - May 5, 2011)\n*[[T\u00e9l\u00e9magino|Playhouse Disney (French Canada)]] (July 5, 2010 - May 5, 2011)\n\n===United States===\n*[[Disney Channel]] ([[Playhouse Disney]]) (September 15, 2001 - May 16, 2008) \n*[[Disney Junior]] (March 23, 2012 - September 3, 2013)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n'''[[Daytime Emmy Awards|Emmy Award]]'''\n*[[29th Daytime Emmy Awards|2002]] \u2013 ''[[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer In An Animated Program|Outstanding Performer in an Animated Program]]'' \u2013 [[Charles Shaughnessy]] for playing \"Dennis\" (won)\n\n==Film==\nOn January 3, 2006, [[Walt Disney Home Entertainment]] and [[Cartoon Pizza]] released a full-length [[direct-to-video]] movie based on ''Stanley''. Entitled ''[[Stanley's Dinosaur Round-Up]]'', the film centers on the titular character as he, along with Elsie, Dennis, Harry, Mimi, Lester, and Marci, team up to save his Great Uncle Stew ([[John Ritter]], who completed his work for the film before he died)'s dude ranch from the greedy Rockin' Rory (an uncredited [[Randy Quaid]]) who intends to buy the ranch and turn it into an amusement park.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n''Channels''\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120320032930/http://www.disneyjunior.ca/en/shows/stanley Stanley on Disney Junior Canada]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120508095912/http://www.disneyjunior.ca/fr/series/stanley Stanley on Disney Junior Quebec]\n* [http://movies.disney.com/stanley Stanley DVDs Disney US site]\n* [http://www.disney.co.uk/DisneyChannel/playhouse/friends/stanley/ Playhouse Disney Official Site]\n\n''Others''\n* {{tv.com show|stanley|Stanley}}\n* {{bcdb |Walt_Disney_Studios/Television/Stanley/ |Stanley}}\n* {{IMDb title|0315068|Stanley}}\n\n{{Playhouse Disney}}\n{{Baha Men}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stanley (2001 TV Series)}}\n[[Category:2000s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2001 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2007 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:American television series with live action and animation]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about children]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about families]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about fish]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about cats]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about dogs]]\n[[Category:Disney animated television series]]\n[[Category:Disney Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Disney Junior shows]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Family Channel shows]]\n[[Category:Peabody Award-winning television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by Disney]]\n", "name_user": "76.202.53.8", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stanley_(2001_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Comparison of triplestores", "text_new": "This is a '''comparison of [[triplestore]]s''', also known as '''subject-predicate-object [[database]]s'''. Some of these database management systems have been built as database engines from scratch, while others have been built on top of existing commercial relational database engines (e.g., SQL-based).<ref>{{cite patent|US|2003145022}} Storage and Management of Semi-structured Data (Use of SQL relational databases as an RDF triple store), 2003</ref> Like the early development of [[online analytical processing]] (OLAP) databases, this intermediate approach allowed large and powerful database engines to be constructed for little programming effort in the initial phases of triplestore development. Long-term though it seems that native triplestores will have the advantage for performance. A difficulty with implementing triplestores over SQL is that although ''triples'' may thus be ''stored'', implementing efficient querying of a graph-based RDF model (e.g., mapping from [[SPARQL]]) onto SQL queries is difficult.<ref>{{cite web\n |title       = The importance of SPARQL can not be overestimated\n |url         = http://www.semantic-web.at/news/jeen-broekstra-x22-the-importance-of-sparql-can-not-be-overestimated-x22\n |last        = Broekstra\n |first       = Jeen\n |date        = 19 September 2007\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20141219084958/http://www.semantic-web.at/news/jeen-broekstra-x22-the-importance-of-sparql-can-not-be-overestimated-x22\n |archivedate = 19 December 2014\n}}</ref>\n\n== Implementations ==\n<!-- In tables, link 1st instance of terms, remove later WP:REPEATLINK(s). -->\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Developed in language !!Latest Version !!Latest Release Date!! Licence\n|-\n| 3store || [[C (programming language)|C]] || 3.0.17<ref>https://sourceforge.net/projects/threestore/files/</ref> || 2006-07-17 || {{GPL-lic}}\n|-\n| Akutan || Go || 