://swat.cse.lehigh.edu/projects/lubm/ Lehigh University Benchmark (LUBM)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110623224454/http://blog.datagraph.org/2010/04/rdf-nosql-diff How RDF Databases Differ from Other NoSQL Solutions]\n* [http://db-engines.com/en/ranking/rdf+store DB-Engines Ranking of RDF Stores] by popularity, updated monthly\n\n{{Database models}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Subject predicate object databases}}\n[[Category:Types of databases]]\n[[Category:Database management systems]]\n[[Category:Lists of database management software]]\n", "text_old": "This is a '''comparison of [[triplestore]]s''', also known as '''subject-predicate-object [[database]]s'''. Some of these database management systems have been built as database engines from scratch, while others have been built on top of existing commercial relational database engines (e.g., SQL-based).<ref>{{cite patent|US|2003145022}} Storage and Management of Semi-structured Data (Use of SQL relational databases as an RDF triple store), 2003</ref> Like the early development of [[online analytical processing]] (OLAP) databases, this intermediate approach allowed large and powerful database engines to be constructed for little programming effort in the initial phases of triplestore development. Long-term though it seems that native triplestores will have the advantage for performance. A difficulty with implementing triplestores over SQL is that although ''triples'' may thus be ''stored'', implementing efficient querying of a graph-based RDF model (e.g., mapping from [[SPARQL]]) onto SQL queries is difficult.<ref>{{cite web\n |title       = The importance of SPARQL can not be overestimated\n |url         = http://www.semantic-web.at/news/jeen-broekstra-x22-the-importance-of-sparql-can-not-be-overestimated-x22\n |last        = Broekstra\n |first       = Jeen\n |date        = 19 September 2007\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20141219084958/http://www.semantic-web.at/news/jeen-broekstra-x22-the-importance-of-sparql-can-not-be-overestimated-x22\n |archivedate = 19 December 2014\n}}</ref>\n\n== Implementations ==\n<!-- In tables, link 1st instance of terms, remove later WP:REPEATLINK(s). -->\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Developed in language !!Latest Version !!Latest Release Date!! Licence\n|-\n| 3store || [[C (programming language)|C]] || 3.0.17<ref>https://sourceforge.net/projects/threestore/files/</ref> || 2006-07-17 || {{GPL-lic}}\n|-\n| Akutan || Go ||  {{dunno}} || {{dunno}} || {{free|[[Apache 2 License|Apache 2]]}}\n|-\n| [[AllegroGraph]] || [[Common Lisp]] || 6.6.0<ref>https://franz.com/agraph/downloads/server?ui=new</ref>|| 2019-08-12 || {{Proprietary}}\n|-\n| AnzoGraph || [[C (programming language)|C]]/[[C++]] || 4.1.0 || 2019-01-30 || {{Proprietary}}\n|-\n| [[Apache Jena]] || Java || 3.12.0<ref>http://jena.apache.org/download/index.cgi</ref> || 2019-05-27 || {{free|[[Apache 2 License|Apache 2]]}}\n|-\n| Apache Rya || Java || 4.0.0<ref>http://rya.apache.org/download/</ref> || 2019-07-27 || {{free|[[Apache 2 License|Apache 2]]}}\n|-\n| ARC2 || [[PHP]] || 2.4.0<ref>https://github.com/semsol/arc2/releases</ref> || 2019-01-25 || {{free|W3C Software License or GPL}}\n|-\n| Attean || [[Perl]] || 0.025<ref>https://metacpan.org/pod/Attean</ref> || 2019-10-25 || {{free|Artistic or GPL-1+}}\n|-\n| [[Blazegraph]] || Java || 2.1.5<ref>https://github.com/blazegraph/database/releases</ref> || 2019-03-19 ||{{GPL-lic}} (v.2)\n|-\n| BrightstarDB || C# || 1.14.0-alpha03<ref>https://github.com/BrightstarDB/BrightstarDB/releases</ref> || 2019-08-18 || {{free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}}\n|-\n| Cayley || Go || 0.7.5<ref>https://github.com/cayleygraph/cayley/releases</ref> || 2018-11-26 || {{free|[[Apache 2 License|Apache 2]]}}\n|-\n| CM-Well || Scala || 1.5.168<ref>https://github.com/CM-Well/CM-Well/releases</ref> || 2019-06-03 || {{free|[[Apache 2 License|Apache 2]]}}\n|-\n| ClioPatria || SWI-Prolog, C || 3.1.1<ref>https://github.com/ClioPatria/Cl